WEBVTT

00:00.994 --> 00:04.679
Friends, welcome to Word on Fire Catholic Ministries.

00:04.699 --> 00:18.377
Word on Fire is an apostolate dedicated to the mission of evangelization, using media both old and new to share the faith on every continent and to facilitate an encounter with Christ and His Church.

00:19.118 --> 00:26.668
The efforts of Word on Fire engage the culture and bring the transformative power of God's Word where it is most needed.

00:26.708 --> 00:27.890
Today,

00:27.970 --> 00:35.998
We invite you to join Bishop Robert Barron as he preaches the gospel and shares the warmth and light of Christ with each one of us.

00:39.421 --> 00:40.562
Peace be with you, friends.

00:40.602 --> 00:47.168
As I record these words, we're going through a tough time in our country without breaks of violence.

00:47.869 --> 00:53.434
Violence against politicians, against public commentators, even against school kids.

00:53.534 --> 00:57.778
It's just been a really rough season.

00:58.434 --> 01:02.640
something else has come to the fore at this time, which is really bothering me.

01:03.421 --> 01:07.526
The tendency of some people in our public life to disparage prayer.

01:08.447 --> 01:17.079
So you'll hear this a lot now when something tragic happens and people offer their prayers and the reactions have had it with thoughts and prayers.

01:17.600 --> 01:22.566
We have to act or keep your thoughts and prayers as time for action.

01:23.988 --> 01:28.274
Even in some of these extreme cases, I think people of prayer are being mocked

01:28.674 --> 01:34.900
as though prayer is just something completely ineffectual that we should leave behind in favor of action.

01:36.662 --> 01:37.603
Can I just say something?

01:38.183 --> 01:43.348
We're like the first generation in recorded human history ever to feel this way.

01:44.229 --> 01:47.653
You go back as far as you can, and I mean across the cultures too.

01:48.433 --> 01:53.578
Human beings have always believed in the power and efficacy of prayer.

01:55.260 --> 01:57.202
I mean, look throughout American history, certainly.

01:57.794 --> 02:05.202
that people pray at key moments of crisis or opportunity, good times and bad times.

02:05.602 --> 02:10.828
And they don't think prayer is just some kind of little, you know, ineffectual private exercise.

02:11.569 --> 02:14.973
No, they think prayer has an effect.

02:16.634 --> 02:27.346
If you would send to somebody prior to, let's say 1975, so of course in my lifetime, if you would say, you know, prayer is a waste of time, prayer is ineffectual.

02:27.970 --> 02:30.934
I think they would have looked at you like you're crazy.

02:32.015 --> 02:38.344
No, we're as a secularized generation, the first one ever to hold this view.

02:39.265 --> 02:44.472
You know, I think of that scene in, it's a wonderful life, the movie that everyone of us knows by heart, right?

02:45.113 --> 02:53.424
And there's toward the end of the movie and there, the narrator talks about the end of World War II and V-Day, everybody wept and prayed.

02:54.045 --> 02:55.186
V-J Day.

02:55.362 --> 02:58.847
everybody wept and prayed and shows people in the church.

02:59.889 --> 03:01.391
Yeah, that's what people did.

03:01.431 --> 03:17.115
This is in the lifetime of my parents, certainly, is people spontaneously prayed because they felt God exists and God is an active agent in the affairs of human beings.

03:18.136 --> 03:22.583
God is not a distant abstraction or a distant force.

03:22.603 --> 03:24.786
God is an active agent.

03:25.250 --> 03:26.391
in the life of the world.

03:27.433 --> 03:29.935
Now, where does this conviction come from?

03:30.036 --> 03:31.878
It's, as they say, been around forever.

03:32.739 --> 03:34.441
Well, it comes from the Bible.

03:34.501 --> 03:36.283
It comes from the Bible.

03:36.944 --> 03:38.325
You can't read the Bible.

03:39.066 --> 03:39.867
Old Testament are new.

03:40.588 --> 03:47.676
And come away with this weird deist idea or much less atheist idea that God either doesn't exist or doesn't care.

03:47.696 --> 03:48.677
No, I don't know.

03:48.697 --> 03:52.882
The God of the Bible is a person who's active

03:53.218 --> 04:05.661
and who knows what's going on and involves himself in the affairs of the world, and who draws from people these great cries of the herds that we call prayer.

04:06.101 --> 04:12.132
Pick up the Psalms, read any of the Psalms, and you find this very deep conviction.

04:13.295 --> 04:17.362
Sometimes, you know, I just think of all the great figures in the Bible.

04:18.018 --> 04:27.953
Abraham, Jacob, Joseph, Moses, Aaron, Samuel, David, Solomon, Isaiah, Jeremiah, Ruth, David, Peter, Paul, James, John, and of course, Jesus himself.

04:27.973 --> 04:29.115
What do they all have in common?

04:29.135 --> 04:30.077
They all pray.

04:30.117 --> 04:35.245
They all pray and they don't think it's an inefficacious exercise.

04:36.827 --> 04:43.858
They pray beckoning God to act, to act.

04:43.958 --> 04:46.482
If you would suggest today any of those figures,

04:46.690 --> 04:48.152
Oh, you know, prayer is a waste of time.

04:48.733 --> 04:49.494
We need to act.

04:50.276 --> 04:56.325
They would have looked you like, are you wanting your mind that your first instinct wouldn't be to call upon God?

04:58.268 --> 04:59.610
That's what's a waste of time.

04:59.670 --> 05:09.806
Now, the story, I will trigger all this reaction to me for our first reading, which is one of my favorites from chapter 17 of the book of Exodus.

05:11.048 --> 05:12.530
It's the time now in Israel,

05:13.186 --> 05:15.609
escape from Egypt, they're making their way toward the Promised Land.

05:15.629 --> 05:19.514
And they're beset by all sorts of difficulties on that famous journey.

05:20.015 --> 05:22.097
And one of them is they come across the Amalekites.

05:22.598 --> 05:25.041
And the Amalekites are like classical enemies of Israel.

05:25.101 --> 05:29.626
They battle Israel at different points in the Old Testament.

05:29.647 --> 05:33.151
So we hear in those days, Amalek came and waged war against Israel.

05:33.451 --> 05:34.092
So what happened?

05:34.573 --> 05:38.898
Well, Moses says, Joshua, you know, get some people, get some soldiers together and let's get into battle.

05:39.426 --> 05:46.013
So if they take action to be sure, the Israelite army forms and they go out in the field to meet Amalek.

05:46.033 --> 05:46.233
All right.

05:46.733 --> 05:54.381
But then we hear that Moses goes up on the hillside overlooking the field of battle and he holds out his arms in prayer.

05:54.441 --> 05:56.082
Now, what's he doing?

05:56.102 --> 05:58.245
It was just a little private spiritual exercise.

05:58.425 --> 06:00.427
No, no, he's asking God.

06:00.867 --> 06:03.830
He's asking God to act, to act.

06:04.411 --> 06:07.794
And it says, as long as his arms were raised in prayer,

06:08.642 --> 06:10.344
The battle went well for Israel.

06:11.125 --> 06:17.574
But then in this kind of delicious detail, Moses' arms get tired as they do pretty quickly when you're like this.

06:18.175 --> 06:23.322
And when he lowers his arms, he stops praying that the battle goes against Israel.

06:24.163 --> 06:31.753
So along come these two assistants, Aaron, his famous assistant and a man named Herr, and they prop up his arms.

06:32.614 --> 06:38.482
And so he's able to keep praying, to keep praying, and then the battle is won.

06:40.034 --> 06:43.458
Okay, prayer, what a waste of time.

06:43.478 --> 06:46.301
Oh, come on, forget about prayer, we need action.

06:47.102 --> 06:51.707
Notice first of everybody, there's not an either or on display here.

06:51.767 --> 06:54.190
It's not as though it's one or the other.

06:54.210 --> 07:08.946
It's both, an army is formed and off they go into the field, but that army is sustained and supported by prayer because God

07:09.058 --> 07:12.683
is an efficacious actor in our affairs.

07:13.524 --> 07:20.113
The action, let's bring them together now, is taking place under the influence of prayer.

07:20.894 --> 07:29.426
God working through secondary causes to be sure, but God working, God working through those causes.

07:31.609 --> 07:37.778
Now, you say, all right, all right, I guess I understand that, but how precisely

07:38.018 --> 07:38.899
does this work?

07:40.240 --> 07:51.831
Well, my honest answer, after many years of living a Christian life and studying theology at the highest levels and teaching it, my honest answer is, I don't really know.

07:52.952 --> 08:01.300
I don't perfectly or entirely know how this happens that our prayer calls forth the activity of God.

08:02.181 --> 08:04.363
I can tell you what's not going on in prayer.

08:05.844 --> 08:07.506
It can't be the case that we're

08:08.034 --> 08:10.838
manipulating God through our prayer, like, hey, don't worry about it.

08:11.279 --> 08:12.541
I got the magic formula.

08:12.601 --> 08:15.626
If I just say these magic words, God will act.

08:15.846 --> 08:18.150
No, no, that's disrespectful to God.

08:18.791 --> 08:26.783
You know, I can compel God to act somehow against His will, or I can control or persuade Him by my speeds.

08:26.803 --> 08:27.544
That can't be right.

08:28.265 --> 08:36.338
Nor can it be right that by my prayer, I'm informing the omniscient God of what's going on.

08:36.578 --> 08:42.765
Lord, by the way, I don't know if you noticed, but we're in a war with the Amalekites and would be really useful if you could help us.

08:42.906 --> 08:43.647
Oh, yeah, thank you.

08:43.947 --> 08:44.908
I didn't realize that.

08:44.948 --> 08:47.591
So let me, that can't be right.

08:47.611 --> 08:51.896
No, no, God knows everything as it unfolds.

08:51.957 --> 08:52.878
God is omniscient.

08:53.318 --> 08:54.820
So prayer isn't that.

08:55.961 --> 08:56.462
So what is it?

08:58.024 --> 08:59.586
Well, maybe this is the best explanation.

09:00.367 --> 09:06.514
John of Damascus famously said that prayer is the raising of the mind and heart to God, right?

09:07.298 --> 09:13.845
So anytime we pray, contemplative prayer, prayer of thanksgiving, whatever, how we pray, we're raising the mind hard to God.

09:14.326 --> 09:19.692
But when we're asking God to act or to intervene, what are we doing in that act?

09:20.533 --> 09:26.259
Is we are making ourselves a kind of channel of God's active energy?

09:27.341 --> 09:35.570
Is there a way we have of linking ourselves to this field of force that is the divine power

09:36.482 --> 09:47.218
Remember that wonderful scene in the gospel when the man who's deaf and with the speech impediment comes and Jesus puts his fingers in his ears almost like he's plugging himself in.

09:47.238 --> 09:54.949
And then he prays to the Father and it's as though this electric current comes from the Father through the Son into this man.

09:55.010 --> 10:06.066
Well, that's an image I have sometimes when we pray, when we praise like we're plugging ourselves in to the source of energy, the source of power.

10:06.690 --> 10:13.880
And maybe the problem is we get so unused to prayer, like we forget how to pray.

10:13.940 --> 10:19.648
We don't bother to pray that we don't find this link to God.

10:22.031 --> 10:28.741
You know, I wonder too, is this why the Bible is so insistent on persistence in prayer?

10:31.044 --> 10:35.410
Again and again, we're told, Old Testament and New is to persist in prayer.

10:36.322 --> 10:40.268
So you're asking God for something, and it doesn't happen.

10:41.089 --> 10:41.770
But don't give up.

10:42.331 --> 10:43.072
Keep asking.

10:43.293 --> 10:43.974
It doesn't happen.

10:45.496 --> 10:46.137
Keep at it.

10:46.317 --> 10:46.978
It doesn't happen.

10:47.719 --> 10:48.400
Keep at it.

10:49.101 --> 10:52.006
You see, because no, we're not manipulating God.

10:52.066 --> 10:53.047
We can't think of it that way.

10:53.088 --> 10:54.610
God does what God wants.

10:54.690 --> 11:02.662
But is there something about the persistence of our prayer that finally, Augustine said this, kind of opens.

11:03.163 --> 11:05.266
It expands the soul.

11:05.474 --> 11:07.956
so as to receive what God wants to give.

11:09.358 --> 11:18.326
So that's the recommendation I have for everybody listening is when you pray with perseverance, pray with persistence.

11:19.427 --> 11:22.911
Here's something else and it's related very much to this prayer action thing.

11:23.812 --> 11:27.115
You know, again, the people today to say, then don't worry about prayer.

11:27.175 --> 11:28.136
Let's get to work.

11:28.917 --> 11:31.559
That's a really dangerous recommendation.

11:32.260 --> 11:32.900
You see why?

11:33.701 --> 11:34.642
Forget about prayer.

11:35.298 --> 11:41.987
Forget about your connection to God who's the source of meaning and value and power and purpose.

11:42.387 --> 11:46.372
God who's the supreme good, forget about all that and get to work.

11:46.973 --> 11:50.818
I guarantee you thereby your work will be a disaster.

11:51.238 --> 12:03.634
Whatever you think you're accomplishing, it will not accomplish what you want because your action, oh, I'm a man of action, not prayer, but your action will be deformed because it's not

12:03.778 --> 12:06.262
informed by the highest good.

12:06.322 --> 12:11.610
So don't give me this, you know, leave prayer to one side and act.

12:12.291 --> 12:15.936
God protect me from actors who don't pray.

12:16.216 --> 12:16.957
You see, I'm driving him.

12:17.518 --> 12:18.580
God protect me from them.

12:19.061 --> 12:26.672
So Israel is actively involved fighting Amalek, but you bet Moses is praying.

12:27.032 --> 12:30.898
He's linking that activity to the purpose of the highest good.

12:32.034 --> 12:35.819
You know, let me just close with this, that beautiful image of Moses praying.

12:35.859 --> 12:39.002
So the great leader, you know, the great high priest.

12:40.464 --> 12:46.511
But his arms are supported by these two relatively minor figures, Aaron and her.

12:48.033 --> 12:49.094
How's the church structured?

12:50.096 --> 12:51.998
Well, there's a fighting church.

12:52.779 --> 12:58.866
Think of all the people who are in an able-bodied way involved directly in the great struggle.

12:59.586 --> 13:04.511
to bring about the kingdom of God, to battle evil, the gates of hell will not prevail against us.

13:04.611 --> 13:07.715
And yeah, we're in the front lines fighting the good fight.

13:09.176 --> 13:15.543
But then behind those who are in the front line are all the people who are praying.

13:16.564 --> 13:23.872
And here I think of like every mass offered, every literature of the hour is prayed by monks and priests and nuns.

13:24.252 --> 13:27.876
Think of all the prayer offered in a contemplative monastery.

13:28.897 --> 13:29.458
Beautiful.

13:29.570 --> 13:34.337
Without that, the action will not be efficacious, but then press it.

13:34.357 --> 13:40.165
Yeah, there's Moses, all these people of prayer, but who's supporting them?

13:40.185 --> 13:42.408
Who are Aaron and her?

13:42.849 --> 13:57.650
Well, think now of all the people in the church who support the prayers, who builds and supports and finances monasteries, who provides the economic support for convents and for parishes,

13:58.178 --> 14:10.270
who supports the work of a parish, enabling priests to say Mass, all kinds of people who are holding up the arms of Moses as he prays so that the work of the church might succeed.

14:12.072 --> 14:17.917
Everybody, that's a much, much better picture of how prayer and action fit together.

14:18.138 --> 14:25.665
Don't believe these people today that want to drive a wedge between them or want to construe prayer as something hopeless in a waste of time.

14:25.925 --> 14:26.546
No, no, no.

14:27.074 --> 14:28.416
Keep this image in your mind.

14:30.300 --> 14:35.570
Our action in the world guided by the great power of God channeled through prayer.

14:36.832 --> 14:37.433
And God bless you.

14:41.801 --> 14:45.388
Thank you for listening to this week's homily from Bishop Robert Barron.

14:45.789 --> 14:50.898
For more resources from Bishop Barron, please visit wordonfire.org.

